France Telecom Signs Union Accord on Gender Equality Issues

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-06-09T19:05:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/france-telecom-signs-union-accord-on-gender-equality-issues.html
France Telecom SA (FTE)  signed a three-year
agreement with three unions to promote professional equality
between women and men, the company said in an e-mailed statement
today.  France Telecom  committed itself to issues including raising
the recruitment of women, ensuring equal pay and limiting the
impact of parenthood on retirement, as well as guaranteeing
equality in career development and equal access to vocational
training, the statement said.  Thirty-six percent, or 33,000, of France Telecomâ€™s 92,000
employees are women, the company said in the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
